The paper deals with algorithms for finding heaviest subgraphs in graphs with real weights assigned to vertices and edges. This falls under the category of graph algorithms, which is a subfield of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of fast matrix multiplication, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses related problems such as computing distance products of matrices, which could fall under computational geometry (cs.CG) or complexity theory (cs.CC).
